						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Narasiṅgayadēva. Year: <hi rend="italic">Chitrabhānu, Tai 10.</hi></hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Begins with obeisance to Śrī Viṉāyaka. This records the remittance of taxes such as <hi rend="italic">sekkāyam</hi> and <hi rend="italic">magamai</hi>, (levied on the land granted to the temple ?) as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi>, for maintaining a lamp and conducting repairs in the temple at Tiruvoṟṟiyūr. It is also mentioned that this arrangement was made with the permission of Īśvara-Nāyakka, who is described as the agent of the king.</p>						

						<p>This record on the grounds of palaeography may be assigned to the 15th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
